{"error": "Expecting value: line 1 column 1 (char 0)", "raw": "These texts appear to be circulars or notifications about various gamma-ray burst (GRB) events detected by the Swift satellite, along with follow-up observations and results from other telescopes such as XRT, UVOT, ROTSE, MDM, and Faulkes Telescope North.

The notifications provide details on the GRB location, coordinates (Right Ascension and Declination), peak count rate, initial flux, and error circles with associated uncertainties. They also report the detection of potential host galaxies or afterglows, along with their locations and magnitudes. Some circulars also include corrective information for errors in previous notifications.

The circulars are usually sent on behalf of the Swift team, as well as other collaborations involved in GRB follow-up observations. They may be used to facilitate rapid follow-up and collaboration among various observatories and researchers studying these cosmic phenomena."}
